        <h2 class="centered no-bottom-margin"><strong><em>Welcome Yelpers!</em></strong></h2>
        <h3 class="centered no-top-margin"><strong><em>(and non-yelpers)</em></strong></h3>
        <img class="fluid blocked max-650" src="2013/Pics_and_Graphics/yelp_logo.jpg" />
        <p class="smallerer med-lines"><strong>Please read: "You</strong> did it! Welcome yelpers (and non-yelpers)... I just wanted to say congratulations to <strong>you</strong>... for what?... for making it to the bottom of my home page. Oh, I am not going to ask <strong>you</strong> for a 5 star yelp review... because I know that it is against yelp's TOS... but, as a fellow Yelper (<a href="http://thomasgohring.yelp.com" target="_blank">http://thomasgohring.yelp.com</a>)...<br /><br />I am simply reminding <strong>you</strong> to check-in on Yelp when <strong>you</strong> visit... and if <strong>you</strong> care to... share <strong>your</strong> honest opinion of my establishment on Yelp... because that <strong>is</strong> what yelpers do, isn't it?... Expect a response from me though... <strong>you</strong> know... because I do get an email the minute you finish your review... So take <strong>your</strong> time... be thorough... share with me and the world what <strong>you</strong> think. Why am I embracing <strong>you</strong>?... <strong>you</strong> ask?... Isn't it crazy? Don't most small local businesses hate yelpers? Yes, it's true, that's what I have heard... But <strong>you</strong> know I am also one of <strong>you</strong>... and because I take <strong>your</strong> feedback very seriously...<br /><br />I like <strong>you</strong> and I value <strong>you</strong>... so while I would love to have <strong>5 star</strong> reviews from all yelpers... I know I have to earn it (please no fake reviews)... I have found that we have made the most improvement because of the feedback from those "less than <strong>5 star</strong>" reviews we got in the past... so happy yelping! So share what <strong>you</strong> like best... and what we could do better. I look forward to reading <strong>your</strong> review on Yelp. Remember I am not asking <strong>you</strong> for a <strong>5 star</strong> yelp review. For our Yelp page: <a href="http://www.yelp.com/biz/kick-butt-coffee-music-and-booze-austin" target="_blank">Click Here</a>.<br /><br />Not a Yelper? Perhaps <strong>you</strong> have a <strong>gmail account</strong>. If you do you can share <strong>your</strong> experience of Kick Butt Coffee Music &amp; Booze here: <a href="https://plus.google.com/108741565480066652893/about?hl=en" target="_blank">Click Here</a>.<br /><br />Of course if <strong>you</strong> would like to share <strong>what you like best</strong> about Kick Butt Coffee Music &amp; Booze ... or what <strong>we could do better</strong>... please email me anytime directly at <a href="mailto:thecoffeeguy@kickbuttcoffee.com">thecoffeeguy@kickbuttcoffee.com</a>"</p>
        <p class="smallerer med-lines righted">Sincerely,<br /><br />
        Thomas "the coffee guy" Gohring<br />
